+# Backend Setup Instructions
+
+The backend is now organized into discrete route, middleware, and utility modules.
+
+## Setup sequence
+
+```bash
+cd apps/api
+npm install
+cp .env.example .env
+npm run prisma:generate
+npx prisma migrate dev
+npx prisma db seed
+npm run dev
+```
+
+## Current backend capabilities
+- JWT auth with login, refresh, logout, and current-user resolution
+- Dashboard metrics endpoint with active, provisioning, suspended, terminated, failed, and usage totals
+- Plans endpoint for provisioning-time plan selection
+- Line lifecycle endpoints for list, detail, create, suspend, resume, and terminate
+- Audit log retrieval
+- Telnyx webhook persistence endpoint
+
+## Environment variables
+Create `.env` with at least:
+- `DATABASE_URL`
+- `JWT_SECRET`
+- `REFRESH_TOKEN_SECRET`
+- `ADMIN_PASSWORD`
+- `CORS_ORIGIN`
+- `FRONTEND_URL`
+- `REDIS_HOST`, `REDIS_PORT`
+- optional Telnyx credentials for real provider integration
+
+## Local infrastructure
+```bash
+docker-compose up -d
+```
+
+That starts PostgreSQL and Redis for local development.
