+# Deployment
+
+## Production stack
+- API container: `apps/api/Dockerfile`
+- Web container: `apps/web/Dockerfile`
+- Reverse proxy template: `deployment/nginx/esim.conf`
+- Compose production baseline: `docker-compose.prod.yml`
+- CI workflow: `.github/workflows/ci.yml`
+
+## Recommended path
+1. Provision PostgreSQL and Redis.
+2. Set secrets from `.env.production.example`.
+3. Build and publish API and web images.
+4. Run Prisma migrations from the API image.
+5. Deploy API behind TLS.
+6. Deploy web with `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` pointing at the API origin.
+7. Configure NGINX or your edge proxy using `deployment/nginx/esim.conf`.
+
+## Build
+```bash
+cd apps/api && docker build -t esim-platform-api .
+cd ../web && docker build -t esim-platform-web .
+```
+
+## Compose example
+```bash
+docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml --env-file .env.production up -d --build
+```
+
+## Health endpoints
+- Liveness: `/health/live`
+- Readiness: `/health/ready`
+- General: `/health`
+
+## Migration
+```bash
+cd apps/api
+npm ci
+npx prisma migrate deploy
+```
+
+## Note
+The web app intentionally uses `npm install` in CI and the container build because a stable lockfile is not bundled in this handoff.
